Detailed Description

A PySound is a wrapper for an FMOD::Event.

It can be used to trigger and re-trigger a sound event, and provides an interface for inspecting various attributes of a sound event.

Returns the length of this sound event in seconds.

Will return < 0 on error, which can be caused by asking for the duration of a looping sound.

bool PySound::refresh ( SoundManager::EventState  okMask = FMOD_EVENT_STATE_READY  ) 

Ensure that the Event* handle inside this PySound is ready to be played.

The first time this is called, this is pretty much a no-op, so it is cheap for one-shot sounds.

void PySound::reset ( SoundManager::EventGroup *  eventGroup = NULL  ) 

This get a new event handle if the event handle has been invalidated.

If a group is specified it will only be reset if it's in that group.
